<title>HONG KONG: HK dollar April M-3 rises 21.8 pct on year.</title>
<headline>HK dollar April M-3 rises 21.8 pct on year.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-05-30</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Hong Kong Monetary Authority gave the following money supply figures as percentage changes on Friday:</p>
<p>				   April '97  March '97   April '96</p>
<p> HK dollar M-3 (year-on-year) +21.8	 +18.4	 +13.7</p>
<p> HK dollar M-3 (month)	   +3.2	  -2.1	  +0.4</p>
<p> HK dollar M-1 (year-on-year)  +17.0	 +13.2	  +6.7</p>
<p> HK dollar M-1 (month)	    +3.8	  -4.6	  +0.5</p>
<p> HK dollar M-2 (year-on-year)  +21.9	 +18.5	 +14.1</p>
<p> HK dollar M-2 (month)	    +3.3	  -2.2	  +0.3</p>
<p>Loans to finance visible trade of Hong Kong (year-on-year)</p>
<p>				     +2.5	  +3.6	 +12.3</p>
<p>Other loans for use in Hong Kong (year-on-year)</p>
<p>				    +25.0	 +23.4	 +12.0</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong newsroom (852) 2843 6441</p>
